  "response": "To help avoid raw rice cravings:\n\n1. Identify potential underlying causes:\n- Nutritional deficiencies\n- Pica condition\n- Psychological factors\n\n2. Nutritional strategies:\n- Eat balanced meals\n- Take mineral supplements\n- Ensure adequate iron intake\n- Consume enough protein and complex carbohydrates\n\n3. Psychological approaches:\n- Consult a healthcare professional\n- Consider counseling\n- Practice stress management techniques\n\n4. Practical tips:\n- Keep cooked rice readily available\n- Substitute with healthier alternatives\n- Drink water when craving occurs\n- Chew sugar-free gum\n\n5. Medical considerations:\n- Get a medical check-up\n- Test for potential mineral deficiencies\n- Rule out any underlying health conditions\n\n6. Potential substitutes:\n- Crunchy vegetables\n- Nuts\n- Rice cakes\n- Roasted rice\n\n7. If craving persists:\n- Seek professional medical advice\n- Discuss potential treatment for pica\n- Get comprehensive health evaluation\n\nRemember, persistent unusual food cravings might indicate a medical condition and should be discussed with a healthcare professional.",
